summary: This is an email chain from July 10, 2019, between Helen V. Cantwell and an unnamed Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) discussing scheduling a call about the Epstein matter. The AUSA identifies themselves as part of the prosecution team, and Cantwell is seeking to discuss an individual referred to as 'Mr. [likely Epstein]'.

persons.name: Helen V. Cantwell
persons.context: She initiates contact regarding the 'Epstein matter,' leaves a voicemail, and attempts to schedule a call with the AUSA.

events.title: Scheduling discussion for Epstein case call
events.description: Email exchange to coordinate a phone call between Helen V. Cantwell and an AUSA on the Epstein prosecution team to discuss the case.

keyFacts: An email chain dated July 10, 2019, shows coordination for a discussion about the Epstein case.
Helen V. Cantwell is attempting to speak with an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) who is part of the Epstein prosecution team.
The AUSA confirms they are 'one of the AUSAs on the Epstein case' and is meeting with the rest of the team.
Cantwell's initial message indicates she wants to discuss 'Mr. [likely Epstein],' though the name is cut off in the text.
The correspondence highlights ongoing legal activity and coordination around the Epstein matter in July 2019.
